20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResidents%20of%20suburban%20Babusapalya%20are%20dependent%20on%20water%20tankers%20for%20their%20daily%20supply%2C%20and%20that%20has%20taken%20a%20severe%20hit%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20four%20tankers%20daily.%20We%20are%20getting%20only%20one%20or%20two.%20We%20are%20facing%20huge%20problems%20over%20the%20past%20two-three%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20resident%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20the%20city%20administration's%20order%20to%20fix%20tanker%20water%20rates%20has%20helped%2C%20a%20resident%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20rates%20have%20stabilised%2C%20but%20the%20problem%20remains%20huge.%20We%20are%20not%20getting%20tankers%20on%20time%20because%20of%20high%20demand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20resident%20of%20an%20apartment%20complex%20in%20the%20area%20was%20leaving%20for%20work.%20When%20NDTV%20asked%20her%20about%20the%20towering%20water%20crisis%2C%20she%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20baby%2C%20it%20is%20very%20difficult.%20Tankers%20are%20not%20coming.%20The%20government%20has%20reduced%20the%20prices%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20coming.%20Even%20if%20they%20come%2C%20the%20water%20is%20not%20sufficient.%20I%20don't%20know%20when%20this%20will%20get%20resolved%20and%20when%20we%20will%20get%20back%20to%20normal%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20they%20are%20hopeful%20of%20better%20times%20once%20the%20monsoon%20comes%2C%20a%20resident%20flagged%20problems%20with%20the%20way%20in%20which%20successive%20governments%20implemented%20development%20projects.%20%26quot%3BThey%20did%20not%20consider%20the%20(overall)%20well-being%20of%20people.%20The%20focus%20has%20been%20on%20building%20apartments%20and%20roads%2C%20but%20we%20need%20to%20work%20on%20the%20groundwater%20level.%20It%20has%20never%20been%20done.%20I%20have%20been%20here%2015%20years.%20I%20have%20never%20seen%20such%20measures%20by%20any%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20people%20are%20waiting%20in%20kilometre-long%20queues%20for%20drinking%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20resident%20said%20he%20took%20a%20bath%205%20times%20over%20the%20past%20one%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBengaluru%20primarily%20gets%20its%20water%20supply%20from%20two%20sources%20-%20Cauvery%20river%20and%20groundwater.%20For%20most%20non-drinking%20uses%2C%20recycled%20water%20processed%20by%20sewage%20treatment%20plants%20is%20used.%20With%20no%20rain%20for%20a%20while%20now%2C%20the%20primary%20sources%20have%20been%20stretched%20to%20their%20limits.%20The%20result%20is%20a%20daily%20struggle%20for%20the%20city's%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authorities%20have%20responded%20with%20fixed%20rates%20for%20tankers%20supplying%20water%20to%20residential%20areas%20following%20allegations%20of%20extortion.%20Fines%20have%20been%20announced%20for%20use%20of%20drinking%20water%20for%20cleaning%20vehicles%20or%20gardening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20water%20crisis%20has%20hit%20hospitals%20too.%20Brookfield%20Hospital%20near%20Whitefield%2C%20one%20of%20the%20parched%20areas%20in%20the%20city%20right%20now%2C%20depends%20on%20water%20tankers%20and%20needs%2024%2C000%20litres%20in%20three%20days.%20That's%20not%20all%2C%205%2C000%20litres%20are%20needed%20daily%20just%20for%20the%20dialysis%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Pradeep%20Kumar%2C%20medical%20officer%20of%20Brookfield%20Hospital%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20recycling%20water%20and%20using%20it%20along%20with%20regular%20water%20for%20washing%20and%20cleaning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBengaluru%20has%20a%20huge%20chunk%20of%20the%20country's%20migrant%20techies%2C%20who%20have%20flocked%20to%20the%20IT%20hub%20for%20the%20opportunities%20it%20offers.%20Now%2C%20they%20are%20looking%20at%20work-from-home%20options%20to%20minimise%20water%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShruthi%2C%20an%20engineer%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWork-from-home%20will%20be%20a%20