0as%20the%20Quest%20user%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%20The%20headset%20also%20had%20to%20be%20in%20developer%20mode%2C%20which%20the%20researchers%20said%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-used-metas-virtual-reality-headset-in-office-in-metaverse-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20Quest%3C%2Fa%3E%20users%20keep%20enabled%20in%20order%20to%20get%20third-party%20apps%2C%20adjust%20resolution%2C%20and%20take%20screenshots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%20the%20researchers%20were%20able%20to%20plant%20malware%20onto%20the%20headset%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20install%20a%20phony%20home%20screen%20that%20looked%20identical%20to%20the%20user's%20original%20screen%2C%20but%20that%20could%20be%20controlled%20by%20the%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20duplicate%20home%20screen%20is%20essentially%20a%20simulation%20within%20a%20simulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20user%20thinks%20they%20are%20interacting%20normally%20with%20different%20VR%20applications%2C%20they%20are%20in%20fact%20interacting%20within%20a%20simulated%20world%2C%20where%20everything%20they%20see%20and%20hear%20has%20been%20intercepted%2C%20relayed%2C%20and%20possibly%20altered%20by%20the%20attacker%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20created%20cloned%20versions%20of%20the%20Meta%20Quest%20Browser%20and%20VRChat%20app.%20Once%20the%20replica%20browser%20app%20was%20running%2C%20the%20researchers%20were%20able%20to%20spy%20on%20the%20users%20as%20they%20logged%20into%20sensitive%20accounts%2C%20like%20their%20bank%20or%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20able%20to%20not%20only%20see%20what%20the%20user%20was%20doing%2C%20but%20also%20manipulate%20what%20the%20user%20was%20seeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20researchers%20described%20a%20situation%20where%20a%20user%20is%20transferring%20money.%20While%20the%20user%20tries%20to%20transfer%20%241%20to%20someone%2C