itutionally%20suppressed%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20current%20and%20former%20lawmakers%20may%20be%20collectively%20entitled%20to%20%2450%20million%20in%20damages%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20vindication%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20the%20principles%20the%20founders%20were%20trying%20to%20achieve%2C%26quot%3B%20Ken%20Cuccinelli%2C%20the%20lawyer%20and%20former%20Trump%20White%20House%20official%20leading%20the%20suit%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECuccinelli's%20lawsuit%2C%20first%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnewsletters%2Finside-congress%2F2024%2F03%2F11%2Fthe-house-gop-eyes-a-new-chance-to-undercut-biden-00146375%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPOLITICO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20filed%20last%20week%20on%20behalf%20of%20Republican%20Rep.%20Rick%20Crawford%20of%20Arkansas%20and%20a%20trio%20of%20ex-lawmakers%20from%20both%20parties%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20hinges%20primarily%20on%20the%2027th%20Amendment%20to%20the%20US%20Constitution%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3ENo%20law%2C%20varying%20the%20compensation%20for%20the%20services%20of%20the%20Senators%20and%20Representatives%2C%20shall%20take%20effect%2C%20until%20an%20election%20of%20Representatives%20shall%20have%20intervened.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amendment%20was%20first%20submitted%20to%20the%20states%20for%20ratification%20along%20with%20the%20amendments%20that%20later%20became%20the%20Bill%20of%20Rights%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20wasn't%20ratified%20until%201992%2C%20over%20200%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20argues%20that%20Congress%20has%20violated%20the%20US%20Constitution%20by%20routinely%20denying%20lawmakers%20an%20annual%20cost%20of%20living%20adjustment%20in%20their%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202009%2C%20rank-and-file%20lawmakers'%20salaries%20have%20remained%20flat%20at%20%24174%2C000%20because%20government%20funding%20bills%20have%20included%20a%20provision%20explicitly%20blocking%20a%20modest%20pay%20increase%20that%20would%20otherwise%20happen.%20Almost%20every%20year%2C%20Congress%20votes%20on%20those%20bills%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20take%20effect%20%E2%80%94%20without%20an%20election%20happening%20in%20between.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20lawmakers'%20salaries%20are%20not%20keeping%20pace%20with%20inflation%20and%20increasing%20under%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20adjustment%20that%20would%20otherwise%20take%20place%2C%20the%20suit%20argues%20that%20their%20wages%20are%20being%20%26quot%3Bvaried%26quot%3B%20by%20being%20effectively%20suppressed%2C%20thus%20violating%20the%2027th%20Amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20a%20situation%20now%20where%20you%20either%20have%20to%20be%20rich%20to%20go%20into%20Congress%2C%20or%20you%20have%20to%20sacrifice%20your%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cuccinelli%2C%20noting%20that%20lawmakers%20are%20typically%20expecting%20to%20maintain%20two%20separate%20residences%20%E2%80%94%20one%20in%20DC%2C%20and%20one%20in%20their%20home%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20calculates%20the%20amount%20of%20additional%20wages%20that%20the%20ex-lawmakers%20are%20owed%2C%20including%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%24753%2C300%20for%20Democratic%20Ed%20Perlmutter%20of%20Colorado%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%24563%2C800%20for%20Republican%20Rodney%20Davis%20of%20Illinois%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%24268%2C839%20for%20Republican%20Tom%20Davis%20of%20Virginia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEstimating%20that%20roughly%201800%20current%20and%20former%20lawmakers%20have%20been%20affected%20by%20the%20routine%20denial%20of%20cost%20of%20living%20adjustments%2C%20the%20plaintiffs%20are%20seeking%20roughly%20%2450%20million%20in%20damages%20from%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20goes%20without%20saying%20that%20this%20is%20unpopular%20with%20the%20public%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busin