2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-bought-fewer-toys-except-lego-millennials-plastic-clutter-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20store%20cilantro%20in%20the%20fridge%20or%20freezer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222127%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Someone%20chopping%20cilantro%20on%20a%20cutting%20board.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61afc8056531110019ceffff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221063%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECilantro%20is%20used%20in%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20dishes%20and%20can%20last%20for%20weeks%20when%20stored%20properly.%3Cp%3EM%C3%B3nica%20Dur%C3%A1n%20%2F%20EyeEm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20not%20stored%20properly%2C%20fresh%20cilantro%20has%20a%20tendency%20to%20wilt%20and%20spoil%20quickly.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20jar%20method%20will%20keep%20cilantro%20fresh%20for%20two%20to%20three%20weeks%20if%20the%20water%20is%20changed%20regularly.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAlso%20try%20wrapping%20the%20stems%20in%20a%20damp%20towel%20and%20storing%20in%20a%20bag%20or%20container.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20usually%20not%20the%20star%20of%20the%20plate%2C%20fresh%20cilantro%20adds%20something%20special%20to%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20dishes.%20%26quot%3BCilantro%20is%20a%20leafy%20green%20herb%20used%20to%20add%20flavor%20to%20dishes%20of%20all%20kinds%20from%20flavoring%20guacamole%20to%20rice%2C%20sauces%2C%20and%20meats.%20It's%20also%20often%20added%20at%20the%20end%20of%20cooking%20as%20a%20fresh%20garnish%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thekitchn.com%2Fauthors%2Fpatty-catalano%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPatty%20Catalano%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20professional%20recipe%20writer%20and%20tester.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20versatile%2C%20bright%20green%20herb%20has%20crunchy%20stems%20and%20delicate%20leaves%2C%20making%20it%20prone%20to%20wilting%20and%20drying%20out%20if%20you%20don't%20store%20it%20properly.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20cilantro%20wilts%2C%20it%20doesn't%20really%20perk%20up%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sophie%20Pennes%2C%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.urbanfarmsla.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUrban%20Farms%20LA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20proper%20storage%20is%20key%20to%20getting%20the%20most%20out%20of%20the%20flavorful%20herb.%20Check%20out%20our%20favorite%20products%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fkeep-your-produce-fresh%5C%22%3Ekeep%20produce%20fresh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20herbs%20to%20ripe%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPennes%20notes%20that%20if%20you%20want%20the%20longest-lasting%20cilantro%2C%20start%20with%20freshly%20picked.%20She%20recommends%20purchasing%20cilantro%20as%20close%20to%20the%20date%20you'll%20need%20it%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Here's%20how%20to%20store%20cilantro%C2%A0%5C%22%3EHere's%20how%20to%20store%20cilantro%C2%A0%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fresh%20green%20cilantro%20herb%20in%20glass%20jar.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61afd24f6531110019cf0439%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20jar%20method%20involves%20submerging%20cilantro%20stems%20in%20water%20while%20the%20leaves%2C%20which%20stick%20out%20of%20the%20top%20like%20a%20bouquet%2C%20are%20covered%20with%20a%20bag.%3Cp%3EBy%20Bonnie%20Photography%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22In%20a%20jar%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20a%20jar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20method%20that%20will%20help%20your%20fresh%20herbs%20last%20as%20long%20as%20possible%20is%20the%20jar%20method.%20After%20purchasing%20cilantro%2C%20Catalano%20recommends%20picking%20through%20the%20stems%20and%20discarding%20any%20bruised%2C%20blackened%2C%20or%20bent%20stems.%20This%20will%20help%20keep%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20bunch%20fresh.%20Trim%20the%20bottom%20half-inch%20of%20the%20stems%20using%20a%20sharp%20knife%20or%20kitchen%20scissors%20to%20help%20them%20more%20readily%20soak%20up%20water.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFill%20a%20mason%20jar%20or%20small%20glass%20with%20about%20an%20inch%20of%20water%20and%20stick%20the%20cilantro%20in%20so%20that%20the%20stems%20are%20submerged%20in%20water%20and%20the%20leaves%20are%20sticking%20out%20of%20the%20top%20like%20a%20bouquet.%20Place%20a%20clean%20plastic%20or%20zip-top%20bag%20over%20the%20top%20creating%20a%20makeshift%20terrarium%20and%20transfer%20to%20the%20fridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFresh%20cilantro%20can%20last%20for%20two%20to%20three%20weeks%20using%20this%20method%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20change%20out%20the%20water%20every%20few%20days.%20Catalano%20notes%20that%20while%20the%20jar%20method%20is%20effective%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20takes%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20space%20in%20the%20fridge%20and%20I'm%20always%20fearful%20of%20tipping%20over%20the%20open%20jar%20of%20water.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22In%20a%20plastic%20bag%20or%20container%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20a%20plastic%20bag%20or%20container%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20have%20the%20space%20for%20a%20jar%20of%20water%20in%20the%20fridge%2C%20you%20can%20also%20store%20cilantro%20in%20a%20bag%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-food-storage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtainer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BAn%20airtight%20container%20in%20the%20fridge%20is%20my%20go-to%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Pennes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20start%20by%20picking%20through%20the%20stems%20and%20removing%20any%20that%20are%20discolored%20or%20wilted.%20Trim%20the%20bottom%20half-inch%20of%20the%20stems%20and%20wrap%20them%20in%20a%20damp%20paper%20towel%2C%20leaving%20the%20leaves%20bare.%20Transfer%20into%20a%20zip-top%20bag%20or%20airtight%20container%2C%20and%20seal.%20Place%20in%20the%20crisper%20and%20check%20the%20paper%20towel%20every%20few%20days%2C%20rewetting%20if%20it%20becomes%20dry.%20Stored%20this%20way%2C%20cilantro%20can%20last%20at%20least%20two%20weeks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20washing%20the%20herb%20just%20before%20using%20will%20help%20it%20last%20the%20longest%2C%20Catalano%20says%20she%20washes%20hers%20before%20storing%20it%20since%20it's%20more%20convenient%20and%20easier%20to%20grab%20while%20cooking.%20Catalano%20recommends%20rinsing%20with%20cold%20water%20and%20shaking%20off%20as%20much%20moisture%20as%20possible.%20After%20wrapping%20the%20stems%20in%20a%20damp%20towel%2C%20she%20loosely%20wraps%20the%20leaves%20in%20a%20dry%20towel%20before%20sealing%20them%20in%20a%20bag.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhile%20you%20will%20sometimes%20find%20dried%20cilantro%20leaves%20in%20the%20spice%20section%2C%20Pennes%20doesn't%20recommend%20drying%20the%20herb%20at%20home%20as%20it%20tends%20to%20%26quot%3Bjust%20fall%20apart.%26quot%3B%20Cilantro%20also%20loses%20most%20of%20its%20flavor%20as%20it%20dries%2C%20and%20is%20much%20better%20used%20fresh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22In%20the%20freezer%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20freezer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22888%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Frozen%20herbs%20in%20an%20ice%20cube%20for%20cooking.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61afd2be6531110019cf0453%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStore%20cilantro%20in%20the%20freezer%20either%20by%20lining%20out%20the%20stems%20on%20a%20lined%20baking%20sheet%20and%20then%20transferring%20to%20a%20zip-top%20bag%2C%20or%20in%20an%20ice%20cube%20tray.%3Cp%3EAhanov%20Michael%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20even%20longer%20storage%2C%20try%20freezing%20fresh%20cilantro.%20Lay%20clean%2C%20dry%20stems%20out%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-cookie-sheet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elined%20baking%20sheet%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20freeze.%20Transfer%20to%20a%20zip-top%20freezer%20bag%2C%20squeeze%20out%20the%20air%2C%20and%20store%20for%20up%20to%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPennes%20points%20out%20that%20another%20effective%20method%20for%20freezing%20cilantro%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bcreate%20little%20cilantro%20ice%20cubes.%26quot%3B%20Chop%20the%20leaves%20and%20stems%20and%20add%20them%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-ice-cube-tray%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eice%20cube%20tray%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Top%20with%20water%20or%20olive%20oil%20and%20freeze%20before%20transferring%20them%20to%20a%20zip-top%20freezer%20bag%20for%20up%20to%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20frozen%2C%20cilantro%20will%20lose%20its%20texture%20and%20some%20of%20its%20bright%20color%2C%20but%20the%20flavor%20will%20remain%20largely%20intact.%20However%2C%20avoid%20using%20it%20as%20a%20fresh%20garnish%2C%20and%20instead%20add%20it%20to%20already%20cooked%20foods.%20Pennes%20notes%20that%20frozen%20cilantro%20is%20especially%20great%20for%20soups%20and%20sauces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Insider's%20takeaway%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInsider's%20takeaway%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20tossing%20fresh%20cilantro%20straight%20from%20the%20shopping%20bag%20into%20the%20crisper%2C%20take%20a%20few%20minutes%20to%20store%20it%20properly%20and%20it'll%20last%20for%20weeks.%20Discard%20any%20bad%20pieces%20and%20trim%20the%20stems.%20Either%20submerge%20the%20stems%20in%20a%20jar%20of%20water%