styled%20in%20a%20question-and-answer%20format%2C%20the%20press%20release%20asserted%20that%20Muslim%20citizens%20of%20India%20would%20not%20have%20their%20citizenship%20affected%20by%20the%20CAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D2013858%5C%22%3Eposted%20to%20the%20PIB%E2%80%99s%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%206%3A43%20PM%20on%20Tuesday%20(March%2012).%20It%20is%20unclear%20why%20the%20release%20is%20now%20unavailable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20contents%20were%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPIB_India%2Fstatus%2F1767556925120544931%5C%22%3Eposted%20to%20the%20PIB%E2%80%99s%20X%20page%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%E2%80%9CCAA%20myth%20busters%E2%80%9D%20but%20have%20since%20been%20deleted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAA%20aims%20to%20provide%20citizenship%20to%20Hindus%2C%20Parsis%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Jains%20and%20Christians%20purportedly%20fleeing%20persecution%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20Muslim-majority%20neighbours%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Bangladesh%20%E2%80%93%20and%20who%20arrived%20in%20India%20before%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20exclusion%20of%20Muslims%20from%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20legislation%20and%20fears%20that%20it%20would%20disenfranchise%20many%20Muslims%20in%20India%20when%20combined%20with%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20sparked%20concerns%20and%20protests%20from%20thousands%20of%20citizens%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliament%20passed%20the%20legislation%20in%20late%202019%20but%20the%20government%20notified%20its%20rules%20only%20yesterday.%20The%20CAA%20could%20not%20be%20implemented%20without%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20home%20affairs%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20questions%20asked%20how%20the%20CAA%20would%20impact%20Islam%E2%80%99s%20image.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20to%20this%20question%20read%3A%20%E2%80%9CDue%20to%20the%20persecution%20of%20Minorities%20in%20those%20three%20Muslim%20countries%2C%20the%20name%20of%20Islam%20was%20badly%20tarnished%20all%20around%20the%20world.%20However%2C%20Islam%2C%20being%20a%20peaceful%20religion%2C%20never%20preaches%20or%20suggests%20hatred%2Fviolence%2Fany%20persecution%20on%20religious%20ground.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20Act%20showing%20the%20compassion%20and%20compensation%20for%20the%20persecution%2C%20protects%20Islam%20from%20being%20tarnished%20in%20the%20name%20of%20persecution%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20release%20said%20that%20Indian%20Muslims%20%E2%80%9Cneed%20not%20worry%20as%20CAA%20has%20not%20made%20any%20provision%20to%20impact%20their%20citizenship%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndian%20Muslims%20need%20not%20worry%20as%20CAA%20has%20not%20made%20any%20provision%20to%20impact%20their%20citizenship%20and%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20present%2018%20crore%20Indian%20Muslims%2C%20who%20have%20equal%20rights%20like%20their%20Hindu%20counterparts%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20Indian%20citizen%20would%20be%20asked%20to%20produce%20any%20document%20to%20prove%20his%20citizenship%20after%20this%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F712816436%2FPositive-narrative-on-Citizenship-Amendment-Act-2019%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20Positive%20narrative%20on%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%202019%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EPositive%20narrative%20on%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fuser%2F286754081%2FThe-Wire%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20The%20Wire's%20profile%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20Scribd%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fembeds%2F712816436%2Fcontent%3Fstart_page%3D1%26view_mode%3Dscroll%26access_key%3Dkey-jaOprIxJElHXGMV4hnUt%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20data-auto-height%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20data-aspect-ratio%3D%5C%220.7066666666666667%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Positive%20narrative%20on%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%202019%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20India%20did%20not%20have%20a%20pact%20or%20agreement%20with%20either%20Afghanistan%2C%20Pakistan%20or%20Bangladesh%20for%20repatriating%20illegal%20Muslim%20migrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20Citizenship%20Act%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20deal%20with%20the%20deportation%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20and%20therefore%20the%20concern%20of%20a%20section%20of%20the%20people%20including%20Muslims%20and%20students%20that%20CAA%20is%20against%20Muslim%20Minorities%20is%20unjustifiable%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20continued%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20question%20that%20asked%20why%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%20needed%20to%20be%20amended%2C%20the%20release%20cited%20a%20mix%20of%20providing%20amnesty%20to%20the%20minorities%20within%20the%20amendment%E2%80%99s%20ambit%20and%20%E2%80%98controlling%E2%80%99%20illegal%20migrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20show%20the%20mercy%20on%20the%20persecuted%20minorities%20of%20those%20three%20countries%2C%20this%20Act%20gives%20opportunity%20to%20them%20as%20per%20the%20evergreen%20generous%20culture%20of%20India%20to%20get%20Indian%20Citizenship%20for%20their%20happy%20and%20prosperous%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20its%20answer%20to%20the%20question%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CTo%20customise%20the%20Citizenship%20system%20and%20control%20the%20illegal%20migrants%2C%20there%20was%20need%20of%20this%20Act.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20introduction%20to%20the%20release%20also%20read%20that%20the%20CAA%20aimed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cshow%20%E2%80%A6%20generous%20treatment%E2%80%9D%20to%20religious%20minorities%20who%20were%20persecuted%20in%20the%20three%20countries%20%E2%80%9Cas%20compensation%20for%20appeasing%20their%20persecution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710266108000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F19114548%2Fpib-hero-image.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpositive-narrative-on-caa-and-indian-muslims-released-by-home-ministry-goes-missing%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Posted%20to%20the%20Press%20Information%20Bureau's%20website%20at%206%3A43%20PM%2C%20the%20release%20said%20the%20CAA%20%E2%80%9Cprotects%20Islam%20from%20being%20tarnished%20in%20the%20name%20of%20persecution%E2%80%9D.%20It%20is%20unclear%20why%20it%20is%20now%20unavailable%20from%20its%20original%20webpage%20on%20the%20bureau's%20site.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpositive-narrative-on-caa-and-indian-muslims-released-by-home-ministry-goes-missing%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Home%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Positive%20Narrative%E2%80%99%20on%20CAA%20is%20Full%20of%20Lies%2C%20Half-Truths%20and%20Really%20Bad%20Drafting%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F12%2F25105717%2FIMG_0686.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20released%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D2013858%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20list%20of%20questions%20and%20answers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20clear%20the%20air%20about%20the%20discriminatory%20nature%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Act.%20The%20document%20makes%20for%20bizarre%20reading.%20It%20is%20shoddily%20drafted%2C%20makes%20improbable%20claims%20and%20is%20full%20of%20half-truths%20and%20even%20outright%20lies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20reproducing%20below%20the%20questions%20posed%20by%20the%20MHA%2C%20its%20answers%2C%20and%20my%20analysis%20(%E2%80%98The%20reality%E2%80%99)%20for%20each%20reply.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3EUpdate%3A%20The%20MHA%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpositive-narrative-on-caa-and-indian-muslims-released-by-home-ministry-goes-missing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeleted%20the%20embarrassing%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20here%20is%20the%20original%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F712812911%2FPositive-narrative-on-Citizenship-Amendment-Act-2019%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Es%3C%2Fem%3Eaved%20as%20a%20PDF%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHome%20Ministry%20preambular%20claim%3A%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3E%20Without%20curtailing%20the%20freedom%20and%20opportunity%20of%20Indian%20Muslims%20to%20enjoy%20their%20rights%20as%20they%20have%20been%20usually%20practicing%20and%20entertaining%20since%20Independence%20like%20other%20Indian%20citizens%20belonging%20to%20other%20religions%2C%20CAA%20(Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act)%202019%20has%20reduced%20the%20qualification%20period%20of%20application%20for%20citizenship%20from%2011%20to%205%20years%20for%20the%20beneficiaries%20who%20had%20%5Bbeen%5D%20persecuted%20on%20religious%20grounds%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20Bangladesh%20or%20Pakistan%20and%20who%20had%20entered%20India%20on%20or%20before%20December%2031%2C%202014%20with%20an%20aim%20to%20show%20a%20generous%20treatment%20to%20them%20as%20compensation%20for%20appeasing%20%5B%3C%2Fi%3Esic%3Ci%3E%5D%20their%20persecution.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20reality%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20have%20no%20idea%20what%20%E2%80%9Ccompensation%20for%20appeasing%20their%20persecution%E2%80%9D%20means%20but%20this%20claim%20is%20a%20dishonest%20one.%20If%20the%20aim%20is%20really%20to%20benefit%20the%20victims%20of%20persecution%20and%20offer%20them%20%E2%80%9Cgenerous%20treatment%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20government%20needs%20to%20explain%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWhy%20is%20the%20benefit%20confined%20to%20refugees%20from%20only%20these%20three%20countries%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWhy%20is%20only%20religious%20persecution%20being%20considered%20grounds%20for%20conferring%20benefits%20when%20there%20are%20other%20forms%20of%20persecution%20that%20people%20in%20these%20three%20countries%20may%20be%20fleeing%20from%2C%20including%20political%20persecution%20or%20persecution%20on%20grounds%20of%20ethnicity%20or%20gender%20or%20sexual%20orientation%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWhy%20have%20Muslims%20being%20excluded%20from%20the%20list%20of%20those%20subject%20to%20religious%20persecution%20when%20there%20is%20evidence%20that%20particular%20Muslim%20sects%20are%20indeed%20persecuted%20in%20these%20countries%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20if%20the%20aim%20is%20only%20to%20help%20non-Muslims%20who%20are%20religiously%20persecuted%20in%20these%20three%20countries%2C%20why%20is%20there%20a%20cut-off%20date%20of%20December%2031%2C%202014%3F%20How%20does%20the%20government%20propose%20to%20treat%20victims%20who%20had%20good%20reasons%20to%20flee%20to%20India%20after%20that%20date%20or%20who%20may%20still%20flee%20here%20to%20escape%20persecution%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%20has%20no%20answer%20to%20any%20of%20these%20questions%2C%20nor%20can%20it%20explain%20why%20it%20took%20four%20and%20a%20half%20years%20to%20operationalise%20the%20CAA%20and%20provide%20this%20%E2%80%9Cgenerous%20treatment%E2%80%9D%20to%20these%20refugees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQuestion%3A%20What%20are%20the%20implications%20of%20the%20Act%20for%20Muslims%20who%20have%20been%20living%20in%20India%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHome%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20answer%3A%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3E%20Indian%20Muslims%20need%20not%20worry%20as%20CAA%20has%20not%20made%20any%20provision%20to%20impact%20their%20citizenship%20and%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20present%2018%20crore%20Indian%20Muslims%2C%20who%20have%20equal%20rights%20like%20their%20Hindu%20counterparts.%20No%20Indian%20citizen%20would%20be%20asked%20to%20produce%20any%20document%20to%20prove%20his%20citizenship%20after%20this%20Act.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20reality%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DZ__6E5hPbHg%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%20several%20times%C2%A0%20in%20the%20past%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20there%20is%20a%20%E2%80%98chronology%E2%80%99%20at%20work%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20policies%20towards%20refugees%20and%20%E2%80%98infiltrators%E2%80%99.%20In%20April%202019%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CFirst%20we%20will%20bring%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Bill%20(CAB)%2C%20every%20refugee%20will%20get%20citizenship%2C%20and%20after%20that%20we%20will%20bring%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens.%20So%20refugees%20have%20no%20reason%20to%20worry.%20But%20infiltrators%20definitely%20have%20a%20reason%20to%20worry.%20So%20understand%20the%20chronology.%E2%80%9D%20He%20added%20that%20the%20NRC%20would%20not%20only%20be%20for%20Bengal%20but%20for%20the%20entire%20country%20because%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20are%20infiltrators%20everywhere.%E2%80%9D%20On%20December%2010%2C%202019%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D--49S5Wx7n8%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EShah%20told%20parliament%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20NRC%20was%20definitely%20coming%20and%20when%20it%20is%20implemented%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20even%20one%20infiltrator%20will%20be%20able%20to%20save%20himself%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20did%20Shah%20mean%3F%20The%20NRC%20is%20a%20process%20whereby%20the%20citizenship%20status%20of%20every%20person%20in%20India%20will%20be%20tested%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20documents%20they%20provide.%20In%20Assam%2C%20where%20the%20NRC%20was%20first%20tested%2C%20the%20results%20were%20disastrous%3A%20some%201.9%20million%20people%20were%20excluded%20as%20citizens.%20These%20were%20Indians%20who%20were%20unable%20to%20produce%20the%20required%20documentation.%20The%20majority%20were%20Hindu.%20The%20purpose%20behind%20the%20CAA%20was%20to%20reassure%C2%A0Hindus%20who%20fail%20to%20satisfy%20the%20NRC%20process%20that%20they%20need%20not%20worry%20about%20being%20expelled%20or%20disenfranchised%20since%20the%20CAA%20allows%20a%20path%20to%20citizenship%20for%20those%20without%20proper%20papers.%20But%20for%20Muslims%20who%20fail%20to%20satisfy%20the%20process%2C%20there%20is%20no%20way%20out.%20They%20face%20the%20risk%20of%20being%20branded%20as%20%E2%80%98infiltrators%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20Modi%20government%20formally%20renounces%20its%20plans%20for%20implementing%20the%20NRC%2C%20the%20MHA%E2%80%99s%20claims%20that%20Indian%20Muslims%20need%20not%20worry%20about%20the%20CAA%20affecting%20their%20citizenship%20is%20simply%20not%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fan-sos-for-indias-democracy-and-media%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewritten%20elsewhere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20consider%20the%20example%20of%20two%20Indian%20women%2C%20one%20Hindu%20and%20one%20Muslim%2C%20who%20have%20been%20married%20to%20two%20undocumented%20Bangladeshi%20men%2C%20one%20Hindu%20and%20one%20Muslim.%20Under%20the%20unamended%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%20the%20children%20of%20both%20women%20are%20considered%20%E2%80%98illegal%20migrants%E2%80%99%20and%20are%20liable%20to%20deportation%20along%20with%20their%20respective%20fathers.%20The%20CAA%2C%20however%2C%20offers%20a%20clear%20path%20for%20the%20Hindu%20Indian%20woman%20to%20live%20a%20normal%20family%20life%20free%20of%20the%20risk%20of%20disruption%20due%20to%20deportation.%20But%20the%20Muslim%20Indian%20woman%20must%20continue%20to%20live%20with%20the%20risk%20of%20expulsion%20of%20her%20family%20from%20India.%20And%20she%20will%20have%20no%20option%20but%20to%20leave%20India%20if%20her%20family%20is%20deported%20and%20she%20wishes%20to%20continue%20living%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIs%20there%20any%20provision%20or%20agreement%20for%20repatriating%20illegal%20Muslim%20migrants%20to%20Bangladesh%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Pakistan%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHome%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20answer%3A%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3E%3A%20India%20does%20not%20have%20any%20pact%20or%20agreement%20with%20any%20of%20these%20countries%20to%20repatriate%20migrants%20back%20to%20these%20countries.%20This%20Citizenship%20Act%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20deal%20with%20the%20deportation%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20and%20therefore%20the%20concern%20of%20a%20section%20of%20the%20people%20including%20Muslims%20and%20students%20that%20CAA%20is%20against%20Muslim%20Minorities%20is%20unjustifiable.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20reality%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20This%20is%20a%20clever%20and%20deceptive%20lie.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2259%2F3%2FA1946-31.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EForeigners%20Act%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Section%203)%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mha.gov.in%2FPDF_Other%2Fact1920_17042017.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPassport%20(Entry%20into%20India)%20Act%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Section%205)%20already%20empower%20the%20government%20to%20deport%20persons%20it%20deems%20to%20be%20illegally%20staying%20in%20the%20country%20(%E2%80%98power%20of%20removal%E2%80%99.%20The%20absence%20of%20a%20pact%20for%20repatriation%20only%20means%20that%20persons%20deemed%20illegal%20are%20liable%20for%20incarceration%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%93%20even%20long-term%20%E2%80%93%20in%20prisons%20or%20detention%20centres.%20Taken%20together%20with%20the%20NRC%20it%20is%20not%20hard%20to%20understand%20why%20%E2%80%9Ca%20section%20of%20the%20people%20including%20Muslims%20and%20students%E2%80%9D%20see%20the%20process%20which%20the%20CAA%20embodies%20as%20anti-Muslim.%20Even%20if%20it%20does%20not%20lead%20to%20deportation%20or%20detention%2C%20the%20fear%20is%20that%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Indians%20who%20will%20be%20mostly%20Muslim%20will%20end%20up%20disenfranchised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWho%20is%20%5Ban%5D%20illegal%20migrant%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHome%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20answer%3A%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3ELike%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%201955%2C%20this%20CAA%20defines%20illegal%20migrant%20as%20a%20foreigner%20who%20has%20entered%20India%20without%20valid%20documents.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20reality%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20In%202003%2C%20the%20then%20Vajpayee%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.refworld.org%2Flegal%2Flegislation%2Fnatlegbod%2F2004%2Fen%2F14043%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eamended%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%20to%20prohibit%20%E2%80%98illegal%20migrants%E2%80%99%20from%20ever%20acquiring%20Indian%20citizenship%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20naturalisation%20or%20marriage.%20In%202016%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fbilltrack%2Fthe-citizenship-amendment-bill-2016%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eamended%20the%20Act%20to%20exempt%20non-Muslim%20%E2%80%98illegal%20migrants%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Bangladesh%20from%20this%20provision%20provided%20they%20entered%20India%20before%20December%2031%2C%202014.%20The%20CAA%20of%202019%20took%20this%20process%20further%20by%20allowing%20the%20fast-tracking%20of%20their%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20as%20the%20law%20stands%20today%2C%20a%20foreigner%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%20or%20Afghanistan%20who%20has%20entered%20India%20without%20valid%20documents%20until%20December%2031%2C%202014%20will%20only%20be%20considered%20an%20illegal%20migrant%20if%20they%20are%20Muslim.%20All%20non-Muslims%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20considered%20illegal%20migrants.%20This%20discrimination%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%20violates%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fprasanna_s%2Fstatus%2F1179746443029925888%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20lawyer%20S.%20Prasanna%20has%20noted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20discrimination%20is%20also%20a%20violation%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20obligations%20under%20the%20International%20Covenant%20for%20Civil%20and%20Political%20Rights%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Finstruments-mechanisms%2Finstruments%2Finternational-covenant-civil-and-political-rights%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%2026%20of%20which%20states%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20persons%20are%20equal%20before%20the%20law%20and%20are%20entitled%20without%20any%20discrimination%20to%20the%20equal%20protection%20of%20the%20law.%20In%20this%20respect%2C%20the%20law%20shall%20prohibit%20any%20discrimination%20and%20guarantee%20to%20all%20persons%20equal%20and%20effective%20protection%20against%20discrimination%20on%20any%20ground%20such%20as%20race%2C%20colour%2C%20sex%2C%20language%2C%20religion%2C%20political%20or%20other%20opinion%2C%20national%20or%20social%20origin%2C%20property%2C%20birth%20or%20other%20status.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20is%20the%20impact%20of%20this%20Act%20on%20the%20image%20of%20Islam%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHome%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20answer%3A%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3E%20Due%20to%20the%20persecution%20of%20Minorities%20in%20those%20three%20Muslim%20countries%2C%20the%20name%20of%20Islam%20was%20badly%20tarnished%20all%20around%20the%20world.%20However%2C%20Islam%2C%20being%20a%20peaceful%20religion%2C%20never%20preaches%20or%20suggests%20hatred%2Fviolence%2Fany%20persecution%20on%20religious%20ground.%20This%20Act%20showing%20the%20compassion%20and%20compensation%20for%20the%20persecution%2C%20protects%20Islam%20from%20being%20tarnished%20in%20the%20name%20of%20persecution.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20reality%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20If%20we%20ignore%20the%20terrible%20drafting%20of%20this%20answer%2C%20the%20MHA%20and%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20explain%20why%20a%20law%20has%20been%20made%20to%20accept%20religiously%20persecuted%20people%20%3Ci%3Eonly%3C%2Fi%3E%20from%20Muslim%20counties%20and%20not%20from%20other%20non-Muslim%20neighbouring%20nations%20like%20Myanmar%2C%20China%20and%20Sri%20Lanka.%20Is%20the%20government%20not%20saying%20that%20there%20is%20something%20unique%20about%20persecution%20in%20Muslim%20countries%20which%20is%20causing%20it%20to%20create%20a%20new%20law%20for%20its%20victims%3F%20What%20does%20this%20tell%20us%20about%20how%20the%20government%20view%20Islam%20and%20Muslims%20as%20opposed%20to%20other%20faiths%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20the%20CAA%20may%20or%20may%20not%20have%20any%20impact%20on%20the%20image%20of%20Islam%20but%20it%20has%20already%20had%20an%20adverse%20impact%20on%20the%20image%20of%20the%20country.%20India%20has%20welcomed%20and%20granted%20domicile%20to%20refugees%20and%20people%20from%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20for%20over%20three%20thousand%20years%20but%20has%20now%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20its%20history%20made%20religion%20a%20criterion%20for%20the%20acquisition%20of%20citizenship%20(and%20right%20to%20domicile)%20for%20refugees%20from%20three%20countries.%20The%20world%20at%20large%20sees%20this%20as%20a%20betrayal%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20values%20and%20culture%2C%20not%20to%20speak%20of%20its%20constitution%20and%20commitment%20to%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIs%20there%20any%20bar%20for%20Muslims%20from%20seeking%20Indian%20citizenship%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHome%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20answer%3A%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3E%20No.%20There%20is%20no%20bar%20on%20Muslims%20from%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world%20to%20seek%20Indian%20Citizenship%20under%20Section%206%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20the%20citizenship%20by%20naturalisation.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20reality%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Since%202003%2C%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%20bars%20anyone%20who%20is%20an%20illegal%20migrant%20from%20acquiring%20citizenship%20of%20India.%20The%20CAA%20opens%20the%20door%20for%20illegal%20migrants%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Afghanistan%20and%20their%20India-born%20children%20who%20are%20non-Muslim%20to%20acquire%20Indian%20citizenship.%20But%20illegal%20migrants%20and%20their%20India-born%20children%20who%20happen%20to%20be%20Muslim%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20barred%20from%20acquiring%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20is%20the%20need%20of%20the%20amendment%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHome%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20answer%3A%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3ETo%20show%20the%20mercy%20on%20the%20persecuted%20minorities%20of%20those%20three%20countries%2C%20this%20Act%20gives%20opportunity%20to%20them%20as%20per%20the%20evergreen%20generous%20culture%20of%20India%20to%20get%20Indian%20Citizenship%20for%20their%20happy%20and%20prosperous%20future.%20To%20customise%20the%20Citizenship%20system%20and%20control%20the%20illegal%20migrants%2C%20there%20was%20need%20of%20this%20Act.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20reality%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20There%20was%20no%20need%20to%20create%20a%20religion-based%20exemption%20in%20order%20to%20show%20generosity%20towards%20persecuted%20persons.%20All%20that%20the%20government%20needed%20to%20do%20was%20to%20say%20that%20any%20illegal%20migrant%20in%20India%20who%20has%20a%20well-founded%20fear%20of%20persecution%20in%20the%20country%20of%20their%20origin%20would%20be%20allowed%20to%20stay%20in%20India%20indefinitely%20and%20be%20eligible%2C%20in%20due%20course%2C%20for%20Indian%20citizenship.%20In%20fact%2C%20this%20is%20the%20route%20countries%20around%20the%20world%20follow%20for%20the%20naturalisation%20of%20refugees%20and%20it%20does%20not%20require%20the%20refugees%20to%20be%20of%20a%20particular%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20are%20the%20previous%20initiatives%20of%20the%20Government%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHome%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20answer%3A%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3EIn%202016%2C%20the%20Central%20Govt.%20also%20made%20minorities%20of%20those%20three%20countries%20eligible%20for%20long%20term%20Visa%20to%20stay%20in%20India.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIn%20reality%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EHere%20are%20some%20%E2%80%98initiatives%E2%80%99%20the%20MHA%20forgot%20to%20mention.%20So%20helpful%20has%20the%20government%20been%20towards%20religiously%20persecuted%20persons%20from%20Afghanistan%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20wider%20neighbourhood%20that%20it%20made%20it%20extremely%20difficult%20for%20Sikhs%20in%20Afghanistan%20to%20get%20an%20Indian%20visa%20and%20flee%20the%20Taliban.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20a%20Sikh%20man%20killed%20by%20terrorists%20in%20Kabul%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fhad-been-waiting-for-e-visa-says-widow-of-sikh-man-killed-in-kabul-isis-blast%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehis%20visa%20for%20India%20never%20came%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202021-22%20alone%2C%201500%20Pakistani%20Hindus%20who%20wanted%20to%20stay%20in%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fjaipur%2Fno-indian-citizenship-1500-pak-hindus-return-in-18-mths%2Farticleshow%2F93699054.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewere%20forced%20to%20return%20home%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20hurdles%20placed%20in%20their%20way%20by%20the%20government.%20Rohingyas%2C%20fleeing%20religious%20persecution%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20have%20been%20deported%20by%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIs%20there%20any%20restriction%20for%20Muslim%20migrants%20from%20any%20foreign%20country%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EHome%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20answer%3A%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3E%3A%20CAA%20does%20not%20cancel%20the%20naturalisation%20laws.%20Therefore%2C%20any%20person%20including%20the%20Muslim%20migrants%20from%20any%20foreign%20country%2C%20seeking%20to%20be%20an%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20can%20apply%20for%20the%20same%20under%20the%20existing%20laws.%20This%20Act%20does%20not%20prevent%20any%20Muslim%2C%20who%20is%20persecuted%20in%20those%203%20Islamic%20countries%20for%20practicing%20their%20version%20of%20Islam%2C%20from%20applying%20for%20Indian%20citizenship%20under%20the%20existing%20laws.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20reality%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20In%20this%20answer%2C%20the%20MHA%20has%20let%20the%20cat%20out%20of%20the%20bag.%20It%20knows%20very%20well%20that%20there%20are%20Muslims%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Bangladesh%20who%20are%20persecuted%20for%20practising%20their%20version%20of%20Islam.%20But%20if%20they%20enter%20India%20without%20valid%20papers%2C%20or%20overstay%20their%20visa%2C%20they%20automatically%20get%20classified%20as%20illegal%20migrants%20and%20are%20thus%20ineligible%20for%20Indian%20citizenship%20under%20existing%20laws.%20So%20they%20simply%20cannot%20apply%20for%20Indian%20citizenship%20under%20the%20existing%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710265864000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F12%2F25105717%2FIMG_0686.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhome-ministrys-positive-narrative-on-caa-is-full-of-lies-half-truths-and-really-bad-drafting%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20document